    "Body": " COVID-19 Screener (EMTs) Medcor Inc - 3.7 Boston, MA Quick Apply Job Details Temporary | ContractEstimated: $36,000 - $52,000 a year6 days ago Benefits Health Insurance Qualifications Customer Service Communication Skills CPR Certification EMT Certification Full Job Description Medcor is looking to hire several EMTs to be COVID-19 Screeners on a temporary basis at our client's worksite located in Boston, MA. These are temporary, non-benefitted positions working 12 hours shifts in a 24/7 environment, and is expected to last 60 days with a possibility of extending. This position provides COVID-19 screening services as per the Medcor Care Protocol. In order to be successful in this role one must possess the following characteristics: Quick Learner, Strong Interpersonal Skills with all Communication mediums, Creative and Innovative, Fosters Teamwork, Demonstrates Leadership Qualities, Strong Organization and Planning Skills, Ability to Solve Problems, but knows when to ask for input and help. Excellent responsiveness and quick follow-up to requests are key. Detailed knowledge about COVID-19 and educating employees through sharing the updates provided by Medcor Clinical Affairs. A typical day in the life of a Medcor COVID-19 Screener Provide screenings to employees who volunteer, using Medcor protocol and non-contact infrared thermometers Provide patient care (where necessary) according to Patient Care Protocol Provide COVID-19 FAQ\u2019s and educational material with daily status updates (as available) from our Clinical Affairs team Site liaison for following preventative practices (proper hygiene, social distancing and other practices) Put on (don) and remove (doff) personal protective equipment (PPE) per company protocol (Medcor to provide training resource as needed) Enter data in Medcor\u2019s database Provide data to client upon request or as agreed to by client Disseminating relevant client policies and info given to us and as directed by client Being a general resource to client and employees General Maintenance of the facility which includes: Sanitization of screening station as per the protocol and at least once per day Sterilization of equipment/instruments used Inventory and ordering of medical and office supplies You Must Have an active and valid EMT Certification and need to provide proof of current certification Have a current CPR certification \u2013 need to provide proof of current certification Be able to check temperature using a thermometer (Medcor to provide training as needed) Be able to wear required PPE for up to 12 hours per shift (face mask, eye protection, medical gloves, gown, safety vest, etc.) Be able to work in an outdoor environment (subject to change) Be able to pass a fit test for a respirator based on OSHA laws and compliance standards (facial hair must not interfere with seal of mask) Have strong English skills Be able to repeatedly climb a 3-step ladder, and perform bending, lifting, twisting, reaching, squeezing, and standing for long periods of time Have strong communication and customer service skills Have strong technology skills (navigate cell phone or tablet & texting) Learn Medcor\u2019s COVID-19 information once hired (provided by Medcor) It\u2019s a Plus If You are bilingual (English & Spanish) Work Environment: The COVID-19 Screener is required to work in a variety of work environments designated by the client. The COVID-19 Screener will be working in a potentially high COVID-19 exposure environment with known and unknown associated health risks. Individuals with underlying health conditions who contract COVID-19 have greater risk for morbidity and mortality as defined by the Centers for Disease Control (cdc.gov) and should consider these risks prior to accepting this position. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. Culture We don\u2019t just advocate for our clients and our patients; we also advocate for ourselves. To learn more about Medcor\u2019s Culture click here. Medcor Philosophy Medcor embraces a set of simple, interconnected practices that everyone can tailor to their own life and work. To preserve our pioneering, entrepreneurial spirit, we impart our values through the ongoing Better@Medcor campaign: encouraging our advocates to make a conscious choice to practice our values, to celebrate and recognize each other via our peer recognition program, and to support one another during tough times. Medcor is a tobacco free and smoke free workplace! EOE/M/F/Vet/Disability Key Words EMT-B, EMT-I "
